<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-03T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="809" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12756:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-03T09:00:00+02:00">July 3, 1941—9
                                            a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>265. My 259, July 1, noon. Head of the Lebanese Government have
                                    sent me signed note giving full details re damage caused in
                                    Beirut by raids during nights June 29th to 30th and June 30th to
                                    July 1st. He concludes with the statement that only objectives
                                    devoid of all military character were hit which has caused
                                    considerable emotion among the civilian inhabitants. Lebanese
                                    Government protests energetically and requests me to intervene
                                    so as to put an end to useless destruction of property and
                                    innocent lives.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>